text: Keith De Casseres (27 May 1910 - 23 February 2003) was a Jamaican sports shooter who represented the West Indies Federation at the 1960 Summer Olympics. He competed in the 50 metre pistol event. ==References== Category:1910 births Category:2003 deaths Category:Jamaican male sport shooters Category:Olympic shooters of the British West Indies Category:Shooters at the 1960 Summer Olympics Category:Commonwealth Games competitors for Jamaica Category:Shooters at the 1966 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Sportspeople from Kingston, Jamaica
